function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> occursin(r"^[A-Z]", word), words)
end
```

This function `keep_only_names` takes a list of words `words` as input. It uses the `filter` function along with an anonymous function to keep only those words that start with a capital letter. The regular expression `r"^[A-Z]"` matches any word that starts with an uppercase letter from A to Z. The `occursin` function checks if the regular expression pattern occurs in each word. The `filter` function returns a new collection containing only the words for which the anonymous function returns `true`.
